The territory under Ukrainian control is #e3d975ff while territory under Russian control is #ebc0b3ff.

Wikipediaâ€™s editors have produced 258 maps describing the evolution of the situation on the ground with the first map published on 24 February 2022 and the last on 17 March 2022. That is an updated map approximately every 2 hours.

The total area of Ukraine is \(603,628km{2}\), which in terms of pixels is given by \(ukrainian\_control\_pixels + russian\_control\_pixels\). You might have noticed that there are a number of arrows and other symbols covering the map, this reduces the accuracy of the territory quantification (if you know how to programmatically remove them from the raw SVG let me know!).

So, based on this very back-of-the-envelop calculation, a pixel is approximately 0.5 \(km{2}\).

And this is how the situation on the ground has evolved.
